- 'Shared their mental health insights' refers to employees who have participated in a 'Mental Health Survey';
- 'Work-life balance that blossoms above average' refers to an average work-life balance score greater than 3.0;
- The query groups the results by department name.

- "past the bloom of youth" refers to employees older than 25;
- "reaching out for support" refers to employees who are seeking treatment;
- "a gardener by their side" refers to the availability of counseling services.

- 'High Risk' is assigned to employees who seek treatment and experience mental health consequences;
- 'Moderate Risk' is assigned to employees who do not seek treatment but experience mental health consequences;
